WEBVTT

00:02.836 --> 00:04.668
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:09.092 --> 00:12.585
<i>(narrator) YOU'RE TRAVELING
THROUGH ANOTHER DIMENSION</i>

00:12.679 --> 00:15.717
<i>A DIMENSION NOT ONLY OF SIGHT
AND SOUND, BUT OF MIND</i>

00:15.807 --> 00:17.548
<i>A JOURNEY
INTO A WONDROUS LAND</i>

00:17.643 --> 00:19.884
<i>WHOSE BOUNDARIES
ARE THAT OF IMAGINATION.</i>

00:19.978 --> 00:21.594
<i>THAT'S THE SIGNPOST UP AHEAD.</i>

00:21.688 --> 00:23.520
<i>YOUR NEXT STOP,
THE TWILIGHT</i> ZONE.

00:31.532 --> 00:33.648
<i>(narrator)
THERE WAS A VILLAGE</i>

00:33.742 --> 00:36.484
<i>BUILT OF CRUMBLING CLAY
AND ROTTING WOOD</i>

00:36.578 --> 00:39.661
<i>AND IT SQUATTED, UGLY,
UNDER A BROILING SUN</i>

00:39.748 --> 00:43.662
<i>LIKE A SICK AND MANGY ANIMAL
WANTING TO DIE.</i>

00:43.752 --> 00:46.790
<i>THIS VILLAGE HAD A VIRUS
SHARED BY ITS PEOPLE.</i>

00:46.880 --> 00:50.168
<i>IT WAS THE GERM OF SQUALOR,
OF HOPELESSNESS</i>

00:50.259 --> 00:52.626
<i>OF A LOSS OF FAITH.</i>

00:52.719 --> 00:56.963
FOR THE FAITH LESS, THE
HOPELESS, THE MISERY-LADEN

00:57.057 --> 00:59.264
THERE IS TIME, AMPLE TIME

00:59.351 --> 01:02.935
TO ENGAGE IN ONE OF THE
OTHER PURSUITS OF MEN.

01:03.021 --> 01:05.934
THEY BEGIN
TO DESTROY THEMSELVES.

01:15.576 --> 01:18.785
[man shouting]

01:18.829 --> 01:20.866
<i>(man)
LADIES AND GENTS,</i>

01:20.956 --> 01:25.666
<i>IT'S ME, PETER SYKES</i>

01:25.752 --> 01:30.121
PETER SYKES,
BACK FROM ST. LOUIS,

01:30.215 --> 01:32.673
STOCKED UP WITH EVERYTHING
THAT'S NECESSARY

01:32.759 --> 01:34.670
FOR KITCHEN AND BARN

01:34.761 --> 01:39.221
AND THE DRY THROAT
AND THE SWOLLEN TONGUE.

01:40.809 --> 01:42.174
[horse whinnies]

02:03.040 --> 02:04.371
HA, HA!

02:04.458 --> 02:06.324
YOUNG MR. GALLEGOS,
I BELIEVE.

02:06.418 --> 02:08.705
NOW, THIS IS A VERY
SPECIAL DAY, ISN'T IT?

02:08.794 --> 02:10.126
NOW, LET'S SEE.

02:10.213 --> 02:12.079
WHAT IS THIS
SPECIAL DAY, EH?

02:12.174 --> 02:13.835
AH, NOW I REMEMBER.

02:13.884 --> 02:16.751
IT HAS JUST THIS MOMENT
COME BACK TO ME.

02:16.845 --> 02:19.883
TODAY YOU GONNA GET HANGED.
[laughing]

02:22.351 --> 02:25.639
TODAY, YOUNG MR. GALLEGOS,
KILLER OF CHILDREN,

02:25.729 --> 02:28.312
DANCES ON THE GALLOWS.
[laughing]

02:32.527 --> 02:36.361
VVELL, VVHAT VVILL IT BE
FOR YOU TODAY, MR. KOCH?

02:36.448 --> 02:40.783
DON'T NEED ANY MORE ROPE, DO YOU?
[laughing]

02:40.869 --> 02:43.406
YOU OUGHT TO SEE THE
FANCY, FIVE-STRAND HEMP

02:43.497 --> 02:45.784
I SOLD THE TOVVN FOR
YOUR PARTY, GALLEGOS.

02:45.874 --> 02:49.367
IT COULD LIFT FIVE OF YOU.
[laughing]

02:49.461 --> 02:51.498
<i>ANY MORE AT HOME
LIKE YOU, GALLEGOS?</i>

02:51.588 --> 02:53.170
<i>[chuckles]</i>

02:53.256 --> 02:57.716
WELL, WHAT WILL BE
YOUR FANCY, MR. KOCH?

02:57.803 --> 02:59.385
WHAT DO I
FANCY, SYKES?

02:59.471 --> 03:01.053
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT I FANCY.

03:01.139 --> 03:02.516
<i>I'D LIKE YOU</i>

03:02.599 --> 03:04.135
<i>TO TAKE YOUR
FAT CARCASS</i>

03:04.226 --> 03:05.557
<i>AND YOUR
LOUD MOUTH</i>

03:05.644 --> 03:07.226
<i>OUT INTO
THE OPEN AIR.</i>

03:07.312 --> 03:08.723
THIS IS A SMALL ROOM

03:08.814 --> 03:12.227
AND IT'S A HOT TIME
OF THE MORNING.

03:14.403 --> 03:15.939
[snorting]

03:17.572 --> 03:19.563
WELL, WHAT
ABOUT YOU, GALLEGOS?

03:19.658 --> 03:21.444
WHAT WOULD
YOUR PLEASURE BE?

03:21.535 --> 03:24.323
NICE HACKSAW, MAYBE?
[laughing]

03:24.413 --> 03:26.654
THERE'S GOING
TO BE A FUNERAL PROCESSION

03:26.748 --> 03:28.614
DOWN THAT STREET, GALLEGOS.

03:28.709 --> 03:30.791
YOU BETTER GO
TO THE WINDOW AND WATCH.

03:30.877 --> 03:32.743
THEY'RE BURYING
THE LITTLE GIRL

03:32.838 --> 03:34.795
<i>THAT YOU MANGLED
UNDER YOUR WAGON.</i>

03:34.881 --> 03:36.337
<i>YOU SOBERED
UP NOW, EH?</i>

03:36.425 --> 03:37.915
<i>YOU REMEMBER
THE LITTLE GIRL</i>

03:37.968 --> 03:39.129
<i>DON'T YOU?</i>

03:39.219 --> 03:40.801
YOU GOT STINKING DRUNK

03:40.887 --> 03:43.595
AND YOU RACED YOUR WAGON
DOWN THAT STREET

03:43.682 --> 03:45.093
<i>AND WHAT YOU DID</i>

03:45.183 --> 03:46.639
<i>TO THAT POOR
LITTLE GIRL--</i>

03:46.727 --> 03:48.718
UH-UH, GALLEGOS.

03:48.812 --> 03:51.395
[chuckHng] HEY, YOU'LL
HAVE PLENTY OF CHANCE

03:51.481 --> 03:53.267
TO MOVE AROUND
THIS AFTERNOON.

03:53.358 --> 03:55.440
<i>YOU'LL BE
ABLE TO KICK</i>

03:55.527 --> 03:56.813
<i>AND KICK
AND KICK.</i>

03:56.903 --> 03:59.611
<i>[laughing]</i>

03:59.698 --> 04:02.656
YOU OUGHT TO TAKE A DRINK
OF THIS, SHERIFF.

04:02.743 --> 04:05.280
IT'S A GOOD TONIC.

04:05.370 --> 04:06.781
JUST THE THING

04:06.872 --> 04:09.910
TO SET YOU UP FINE
FORA HANGING.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.287
MAKES YOU STRONG
AND FIRM.

04:12.377 --> 04:14.243
HERE, FEEL THIS.

04:14.337 --> 04:17.204
I DON'T TOUCH
DOG MEAT, SYKES.

04:17.298 --> 04:20.007
YOU TALK BIG
BEHIND A BADGE, KOCH.

04:20.093 --> 04:25.384
JUST SOUNDS BIG TO YOU BECAUSE
YOU'RE A MIDGET, SYKES.

04:25.474 --> 04:28.683
YOU KNOW, I ALWAYS HAD
A LITTLE QUESTION ABOUT YOU.

04:28.769 --> 04:32.012
YOU ALWAYS HAD A THING
FOR FOREIGNERS AND STRAYS

04:32.105 --> 04:33.721
BUT YOU'RE
MIGHTY TIGHT-LIPPED

04:33.815 --> 04:35.726
WHEN IT COMES TO
ONE OF YOUR OWN.

04:35.817 --> 04:39.481
YOU'RE NOT MY OWN, SYKES,
SO DON'T CLAIM ANY KINSHIP.

04:39.571 --> 04:40.732
AS FOR THAT BOY
IN THERE

04:40.822 --> 04:42.324
HE HAD HIS TRIAL

04:42.407 --> 04:44.523
AND TODAY HE'S GOING
TO SWING FOR IT.

04:44.618 --> 04:46.529
THERE'S NOTHING
IN HIS SENTENCE

04:46.620 --> 04:48.577
THAT SAYS HE'S GOT
TO BE TORMENTED

04:48.663 --> 04:52.281
BY A PIG WHO SELLS
TRINKETS AT FUNERALS.

04:52.375 --> 04:53.581
<i>GO ON, SYKES.</i>

04:53.668 --> 04:55.659
GET OUT OF HERE.

05:13.438 --> 05:17.477
VVHEN THIS DAY IS OVER, VVHICH
ONE VVILL YOU VVEEP FOR, KOCH?

05:20.028 --> 05:23.191
I HAVE TEARS ENOUGH FOR BOTH.

05:50.684 --> 05:53.767
MR. AND MRS. CANFIELD, I'M
REAL SORRY ABOUT THIS.

05:53.854 --> 05:56.221
MY CONDOLENCES
TO YOU.

05:56.314 --> 05:57.475
THIS AFTERNOON
WILL BE

05:57.566 --> 05:58.806
A LOT MORE
CHEERY.

05:58.900 --> 06:00.436
YES, WE GOING
TO STRING UP

06:00.527 --> 06:02.518
THE DIRTY LITTLE
ANIMAL THAT DONE THIS.

06:02.612 --> 06:03.898
SHE GONNA
BE AVENGED.

06:03.989 --> 06:05.400
YOU CAN SET
YOUR MIND TO REST

06:05.490 --> 06:07.026
ON THAT SCORE.

06:07.117 --> 06:09.734
WE'LL STRING UP THAT
MANGLER OF CHILDREN

06:09.828 --> 06:11.910
IF IT'S THE LAST
THING WE DO.

06:19.963 --> 06:22.796
SOME OTHER TIME,
HUH, SYKES?

06:22.883 --> 06:24.294
SOME OTHER TIME

06:24.384 --> 06:26.216
YOU ACT LIKE A MAN
WITH NO BRAINS

06:26.303 --> 06:27.839
BUT NOT NOW.

06:27.929 --> 06:30.466
NOW YOU KEEP QUIET.

06:30.557 --> 06:32.093
NOW, LOOK AT THAT,
WILL YOU?

06:32.142 --> 06:34.008
<i>AIN'T THAT
THE MOST GALL</i>

06:34.102 --> 06:35.684
<i>YOU EVER SEEN
IN ONE PLACE?</i>

06:35.770 --> 06:38.603
GALLEGOS' OLD MAN
SHOWS HIS FACE IN TOWN

06:38.690 --> 06:40.226
IN BROAD DAYLIGHT

06:40.317 --> 06:43.309
AND DURING THE FUNERAL
PROCESSION, TOO.

06:43.403 --> 06:47.021
SOMEBODY OUGHT TO TAKE
A HORSEWHIP TO THAT--

06:47.115 --> 06:48.856
THAT--

06:48.950 --> 06:50.566
<i>[suspense music]</i>

07:07.469 --> 07:09.710
<i>(girl)
MY FATHER WISHES ME</i>

07:09.804 --> 07:11.795
TO TELL YOU THAT--

07:11.890 --> 07:13.301
MY FATHER
WISHES FOR ME

07:13.391 --> 07:14.722
TO TELL YOU

07:14.809 --> 07:17.016
THAT HIS HEART
IS BROKEN.

07:17.103 --> 07:19.140
THAT IF HE COULD--

07:19.230 --> 07:21.437
IF HE COULD GIVE--

07:21.524 --> 07:24.061
[sniffs, Spanish accent]
HIS OWN LIFE IN RETURN.

07:24.152 --> 07:29.022
HIS OWN LIFE
IN RETURN, ESTRELITA.

07:29.115 --> 07:32.028
HIS OWN LIFE
IN RETURN, HE WOULD.

07:32.118 --> 07:35.861
HE WOULD DO SO
WITH GREAT WILLINGNESS.

07:35.956 --> 07:38.072
HE, HE UNDERSTANDS--

07:38.166 --> 07:40.157
GET OUT OF THE WAY,
LITTLE GIRL.

07:40.251 --> 07:42.162
GET OUT OF THE WAY.

07:42.253 --> 07:44.836
<i>CAN'T YOU SEE--</i>

07:44.923 --> 07:46.539
CAN'T YOU SEE

07:46.633 --> 07:49.216
THAT WE'RE BURYING
OUR DAUGHTER TODAY?

07:54.349 --> 07:55.885
<i>[suspense music]</i>

08:20.208 --> 08:21.790
OH, PLEASE, PLEASE.

08:21.876 --> 08:24.288
MY SON DID NOT MEAN TO DO IT.

08:24.379 --> 08:26.461
<i>HE-- HE'S A LOVER
OF CHILDREN</i>

08:26.548 --> 08:27.788
<i>AS YOU ALL ARE.</i>

08:27.882 --> 08:29.589
HE'S A LOVER
OF CHILDREN.

08:29.676 --> 08:30.882
[thud]

08:30.969 --> 08:32.424
(Koch)
HEY, OZZIE!

08:32.511 --> 08:34.173
<i>[in Spanish]
VA YASEA LA CASA.</i>

08:34.264 --> 08:37.256
<i>NO SE LE
NECESITA AQUI.</i>

08:37.350 --> 08:38.932
HE'S NOT
NEEDED HERE.

08:39.019 --> 08:41.681
IS THAT VVHAT YOU SAY
TO YOUR OLD FATHER?

08:41.770 --> 08:43.386
FATHER, TAKE
ESTRELITA HOME.

08:43.481 --> 08:44.983
THEY WILL HURT YOU
IF YOU STAY.

08:45.066 --> 08:46.852
PLEASE, GO HOME NOW.

08:46.943 --> 08:49.685
<i>[in Spanish] VA YASEA
LA CASA, POE' FAVOR.</i>

08:51.948 --> 08:52.938
LUIS.

08:53.033 --> 08:54.444
LUIS.

08:54.534 --> 08:56.070
MY LUCKY COIN.

08:56.161 --> 08:59.654
IT IS SAID ONE CAN
MAKE A WISH ON IT.

08:59.748 --> 09:01.910
<i>(Koch)
GO HOME, OLD MAN.</i>

09:02.000 --> 09:04.037
MAKE YOUR PRAYERS
AND MAKE YOUR WISHES.

09:04.127 --> 09:05.458
LUIS IS RIGHT.

09:05.545 --> 09:08.913
<i>YOU'LL DO
NO GOOD HERE.</i>

09:09.007 --> 09:13.171
YOU NEVER BEEN DRUNK,
MR. SHERIFF?

09:13.261 --> 09:19.177
<i>YOU NEVER FELT SUCH
MISERY RISING IN YOU</i>

09:19.267 --> 09:21.850
THAT SALVATION SEEMED
TO LOOK AT YOU

09:21.936 --> 09:24.928
FROM ONLY OUT OF A BOTTLE?

09:25.023 --> 09:28.311
YOU NEVER FELT PAIN?

09:28.401 --> 09:32.486
SUCH PAIN THAT YOU HAD
TO RIDE THROUGH THE NIGHT

09:32.572 --> 09:35.280
AND NOT LOOK BEHIND YOU?

09:35.366 --> 09:39.985
MY SON WAS HUNGRY
AND HE FELT SUCH PAIN

09:40.080 --> 09:43.539
AND HE DRANK TOO MUCH.

09:43.625 --> 09:46.367
<i>HE RODE
DOWN THE STREET</i>

09:46.461 --> 09:50.045
<i>NOT LOOKING, NOT SEEING.</i>

09:50.131 --> 09:54.295
AND HE HAD A SADNESS,

09:54.385 --> 09:56.672
DEEP INSIDE.

09:56.763 --> 10:01.303
SADNESS THAT THERE
WAS NOT ENOUGH TO EAT

10:01.392 --> 10:04.635
SADNESS THAT HE HAD NO WORK

10:04.729 --> 10:08.518
SADNESS THE EARTH
ALL AROUND HIM

10:08.608 --> 10:13.774
WAS GROWING BARREN
IN THE SUN.

10:13.863 --> 10:17.902
HE DID NOT SEE
THE LITTLE GIRL.

10:17.992 --> 10:23.237
HE NEVER SAW HER--
FOR AN INSTANT.

10:37.178 --> 10:38.509
PSST, LITTLE GIRL.

10:38.596 --> 10:41.509
WAIT.

10:41.599 --> 10:43.010
NOW, YOU STAY HERE.

10:43.101 --> 10:45.593
I WON'T HURT YOU.
DON'T BE AFRAID.

10:45.687 --> 10:49.055
YOU GO TELL YOUR PAPA--
YOU UNDERSTAND?

10:49.149 --> 10:51.686
TELL YOUR PAPA
I WANT TO HELP HIM.

10:51.776 --> 10:56.270
YOU TELL HIM THAT HIS COIN IS NO GOOD.
IT'S VVORTHLESS.

10:56.364 --> 10:58.571
BUT THAT I HAVE
A MAGIC DUST

10:58.658 --> 11:00.615
THAT TURNS HATE
INTO LOVE

11:00.702 --> 11:03.239
BUT IT IS VERY,
VERY PRECIOUS

11:03.329 --> 11:06.321
VERY EXPENSIVE,
<i>COMPRENDE?</i>

11:06.416 --> 11:08.703
UNDERSTAND? NOW,

11:08.793 --> 11:11.000
NOW, YOU TELL
YOUR PAPA

11:11.087 --> 11:13.875
TO BRING 100 PESOS
TO MY ROOM

11:13.965 --> 11:15.797
IN ONE HOUR

11:15.884 --> 11:19.172
AND I WILL SELL HIM
THE MAGIC DUST

11:19.262 --> 11:22.846
THAT MAKES PEOPLE
LOVE AND FORGIVE.

11:22.932 --> 11:24.263
YOU UNDERSTAND, EH?

11:24.350 --> 11:26.432
TELL <i>YOUR</i> PAPA,
<i>COMPRENDE?</i>

11:26.519 --> 11:28.681
GOOD, NOW YOU GO.

11:28.771 --> 11:32.264
[chuckHng]

11:32.358 --> 11:35.225
MAGIC DUST.

11:43.745 --> 11:45.406
[chuckles]

11:53.213 --> 11:54.920
[laughs viciously]

11:57.300 --> 12:02.215
100 PESOS OF WORTH
OF MAGIC DUST.

12:02.305 --> 12:04.137
[roars with laughter]

12:22.742 --> 12:26.610
IT SHOULD BE A GOOD
ATTENDANCE TODAY.

12:26.704 --> 12:29.787
WHEN WAS IT
GOD MADE PEOPLE?

12:29.874 --> 12:32.115
WAS IT
THE SIXTH DAY?

12:32.210 --> 12:35.623
HE SHOULD HA\/E
STOPPED ON THE FIFTH.

12:35.672 --> 12:40.587
THEY'RE TIRED
OF HATING THIS PLACE.

12:40.677 --> 12:42.384
THE SUN,

12:42.470 --> 12:45.337
THE GROUND THAT IS
DEAD UNDER YOUR FEET.

12:45.431 --> 12:50.551
THEY MUST GO OUT AND FIND
SOMETHING ELSE TO HATE.

12:50.645 --> 12:52.306
<i>[approaching horses]</i>

12:55.024 --> 12:57.641
(Koch) THIS ISN'T A
CARNIVAL, ROGERS.

12:57.735 --> 12:59.988
IT'S A HANGING.

13:00.029 --> 13:01.406
YOU MEAN THE KIDS?

13:01.489 --> 13:03.105
THEY AIN'T NEVER
SEEN A HANGING.

13:03.199 --> 13:04.360
I FIGURED
IT WAS TIME.

13:04.450 --> 13:05.986
WHY?

13:06.077 --> 13:08.444
<i>WHY NOT? THEY'LL
LEARN A LESSON.</i>

13:08.538 --> 13:12.782
THEY'LL SEE VVHAT HAPPENS
TO DRUNKS THAT KILL KIDS.

13:12.875 --> 13:15.583
I GUESS
THAT'S PRETTY VITAL.

13:15.670 --> 13:17.832
HOW DO YOU TEACH THEM
PAIN, ROGERS?

13:17.922 --> 13:21.506
<i>SHOOT ONE OF THEM
IN THE ARM?</i>

13:21.592 --> 13:24.801
ALL RIGHT, YOU KIDS.

13:24.887 --> 13:27.140
GET DOWN
AND STAY TOGETHER.

13:32.979 --> 13:37.018
IS THAT THE MAN THEY'RE
GOING TO PUT THE ROPE ON?

13:38.609 --> 13:40.145
SI, LITTLE ONE.

13:40.236 --> 13:41.522
I AM THE MAN.

13:41.612 --> 13:43.865
WILL IT HURT?

13:46.034 --> 13:48.992
IF GOD WILLS IT.

13:49.078 --> 13:51.331
GO ON, BOY.

13:55.084 --> 13:56.540
GET READY, LUIS.

13:56.627 --> 14:00.120
IT'S ABOUT THAT TIME.

14:00.214 --> 14:02.205
I'M READY, SHERIFF.

14:02.300 --> 14:04.211
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

14:47.595 --> 14:49.461
(man) COME ON, LET'S
GET IT OVER WITH.

14:49.555 --> 14:51.546
(man 2) SHOULD'\/E
DONE THAT IN THE JAIL,

14:51.641 --> 14:53.257
HANG HIM!

14:53.351 --> 14:56.594
VVHAT ARE VVE VVAITING FOR?
LET'S GET TO IT.

14:56.687 --> 14:59.600
COME ON, SHERIFF,
DO YOUR DUTY.

14:59.690 --> 15:01.772
(man 3)
GET IT OVER WITH.

15:05.947 --> 15:08.279
[wind howling]

15:08.324 --> 15:10.440
[chuckHng]

15:30.847 --> 15:32.212
THE LITTLE GIRL
TOLD YOU?

15:32.306 --> 15:33.637
YES, SHE TOLD ME.

15:33.724 --> 15:35.761
SHE SAID THAT
YOU HAD THE DUST.

15:35.852 --> 15:37.388
DUST WITH
MAGIC PROPERTIES.

15:37.478 --> 15:39.344
THAT'S THE IDEA,
OLD MAN.

15:39.439 --> 15:42.227
LITTLE OF THIS SPRINKLED
OVER THE HEADS IN THE CROVVD

15:42.316 --> 15:44.899
VVILL MAKE THEM FEEL
SYMPATHY FOR YOUR SON.

15:44.986 --> 15:47.102
IT'S VERY RARE.
MAGIC, YOU KNOW.

15:47.196 --> 15:49.107
YOU BROUGHT MONEY
WITH YOU?

15:49.198 --> 15:51.360
YES.
[clinking]

15:51.451 --> 15:52.657
GOLD PIECES?

15:52.702 --> 15:53.908
WHERE DID YOU
GET THEM?

15:53.995 --> 15:55.406
ALL MY FRIENDS.

15:55.496 --> 15:57.658
ALL MY FRIENDS WENT
INTO THE CITY.

15:57.748 --> 16:00.957
ONE SOLD A WAGON,
ANOTHER SOLD A HORSE,

16:01.043 --> 16:02.579
SOME BORROWED.

16:02.670 --> 16:07.335
WE GOT MANY PESOS
AND WE CONVERTED THEM.

16:07.425 --> 16:09.837
IT WILL WORK,
MR. SYKES?

16:09.927 --> 16:12.589
THE MAGIC DUST,
IT WILL WORK?

16:12.680 --> 16:14.045
YES.

16:14.140 --> 16:16.598
YOU SOLD THE ROPE
TO HANG MY SON.

16:16.684 --> 16:19.551
NOW YOU SELL ME THAT
WHICH WILL SAVE HIM?

16:19.645 --> 16:22.182
VVELL, I'M A BUSINESSMAN, MR.
GALLEGOS.

16:22.273 --> 16:24.685
I SELL THAT
WHICH IS NEEDED.

16:24.775 --> 16:26.436
I MAKE
NO DISTINCTIONS.

16:26.527 --> 16:27.813
THIS WILL WORK.

16:27.904 --> 16:30.566
I TOLD YOU,
IT'S MAGIC.

16:30.656 --> 16:32.363
<i>[suspense music]</i>

16:37.246 --> 16:39.032
[chuckles]

16:39.123 --> 16:41.455
LUIS!

16:41.542 --> 16:42.657
LUIS!

16:42.752 --> 16:43.992
I'M COMING, MY SON.

16:44.086 --> 16:46.043
<i>I'M COMING!</i>

16:46.130 --> 16:48.246
[chuckHng] THROW SOME
OVER THEIR HEADS!

16:48.341 --> 16:50.457
AND THEN
WATCH THE MAGIC.

16:50.551 --> 16:54.089
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT. THEN WATCH THE MAGIC!
[roaring with laughter]

17:01.187 --> 17:03.178
STRING HIM UP. VVE
VVAITED LONG ENOUGH.

17:03.272 --> 17:04.887
<i>(man)
LET'S NOT STALL IT.</i>

17:04.982 --> 17:06.643
<i>(man 2)
GET IT OVER WITH.</i>

17:06.733 --> 17:09.066
<i>(man 3)
